  "text": " Okay, let's explain in five minutes how we can develop a lean approach. Firstly, you have to have a vision of where you want to be in three years, in five years. How to develop this vision? Firstly, you have to do some reflection about where you are, what are your difficulties, what difficulties you want to overcome. And secondly, it's very important to understand what are the expectations of your customers. Please meet your customers, what they expect from you. And thirdly, it's also to observe your competitors and what the competitors are doing and what you have to do to stay the best in class within your competitors' world. OK, you have defined your vision. Now you have to communicate this vision. means you have to explain to 100% of your members, say deeply, what are the vision, where you want to be, and where they will be in three years, in five years. And you do, say, kind of communication meeting, once or twice per year, and after, regularly, means on a monthly basis to come back on where you are how one activity or another activities is progressing And I tourism okay sometimes what are the difficulties what are the success and always recognize what the member did to contribute to the achievement of the vision or the activities. Communication is very important. Of course, you know where you are, you know where you want to be, means you measure the gaps. Where I am today in terms of production performance means where I want to be, what I have to modify, for example in maintenance organizations, what I have to modify within my supply chain, all these kind of activities, all kind of gaps. And you define your activities means to fulfill the gaps you observe and you measure. One important point is your management. It means your manager has to be your leader. It means they will guide, they will facilitate, they will innovate, they will develop. And what we expect from your manager is to be able to cascade the vision of the company within their scope of activities. For example, within a division, within a department, within a section. And that is very important. And you have to define your management style means you want to have a participative approach means you have to develop what we call a reverse pyramid means 100 of your members will contribute to the achievement of the vision and will contribute to develop a continuous improvement. Meaning for that, you have to train them, to train them in the continuous improvement method. I will take the example of members. For me, the best methodology is to develop the quality circle approach, where the member, they will select by themselves one concern on which they want to work, and they will apply a methodology, a clear approach, identify the cause, and they will confirm effectively the cause they identify are the good cause. they will be able to develop improvement activity to solve the cause and they will standardize what they implement and they will keep effectively the problem on which they work and of course you have to define the organization you have to define the budget because you allow members to work on the problem that means you have to give time to them means you have to budget, you have to identify clearly what will be the cost of the time you will give to members but of course you will have a payback thanks to the activities they will develop You have to visualize all the activities you develop at the president level but also in the workshop It means the visualization of activities of great circle visualization on which your team leader will work with their members, and to review. I think it's important to review regularly all these activities, and the role, again, of the management is to coach, to guide and to support all the members in their continuous improvement activities. And finally, one important point, thanks to all these activities, you will improve your performance. Meaning you will have extra resources. Means you have to anticipate these extra resources and how to use these extra resources to develop your growth. and try to effectively develop gross opportunities to use effectively the extra resources and the performance you will have thanks to Lean Development Approach. That's what I wanted to say in five minutes about Lean.",
